|   Dimension   |   Teaching Intention   |   Description   |
|---------------|------------------------|-----------------|
| Emotional     | Stimulate Interest (SI) | Use affective or motivational language to arouse studentsâ€™ curiosity and intrinsic interest in learning content. |
|               | Emotional Support and Feedback (ESF) | Provide encouragement, praise, or emotional reassurance to reinforce learner confidence and sustain positive emotional experiences. |
| Cognitive     | Knowledge Instruction (KI) | Deliver factual, conceptual, or procedural knowledge through explanation, description, or demonstration. |
|               | Summarization (SU) | Review or consolidate key concepts or previously learned content to reinforce understanding. |
|               | Guide Thinking (GT) | Use questions or prompts to stimulate analytical, reflective, or higher-order thinking. |
| Interactional | Increase Participation (IP) | Prompt or invite students to enter the interactional flow through verbal responses or learning activities. |
|               | Classroom Management (CM) | Organize and regulate classroom order or instructional procedures through verbal directives. |
|               | Promote Collaborative Learning (PCL) | Structure and encourage peer discussion, cooperation, and joint problem-solving activities. |


|   Teaching Intention   |   Sample Size   |   Examples                                                               |
|------------------------|-----------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| SI                     | 253             | Class, I have a riddle for you. Would you like to give it a try?         |
| ESF                    | 3627            | I would like to commend [name] for her excellent contribution.           |
| KI                     | 6508            | Another form of Earth's movement is its revolution.                      |
| SU                      | 331             | Today, we learned electric motor structure and rotational principles.    |
| GT                     | 9270            | What are the factors that affect internal energy?                        |
| IP                     | 4175            | Let's ask the students from Group 5.                                     |
| CM                     | 1852            | Class, please have a seat.                                               |
| PCL                    | 266             | Alright, discuss it with your partner.                                   |

